<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-13T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-13T11:00:00-05:00" n="804" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d804">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/19849</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-13T09:00:00-07:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1916, 9 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Tension in Chihuahua temporarily relieved by apparent retirement of Villa
                            toward Urado line. Developments there hanging <pb facs="0691" n="615" xml:id="pg_615"/> upon promptness of arrival of Murguia troops and
                            establishment of communication with south. Developments in Juarez
                            hanging upon financial ability of new party to buy garrison.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>